Prior to Confluence 4 we had the ability to search macro attributes. For example, we could search for a user specified in the user-profile macro on various pages. When a user leaves the company, we want to be able to find and fix these references in that macro. However, this is no longer possible in Confluence. There was a plugin available that might have worked for this (https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-macro-indexer-plugin), but it is no longer supported as of Confluence 4.3.7. (We are currently on 5.2.5 and planning to move to 5.4.4 soon). So this is a feature request for the ability to search for macro attributes. I would envision the search syntax to be something like:
macroName:<name>* macroAttribute:<attribute> 
Thanks for your consideration.

